	> Open source build management system
	> It is built on ANT, MAven and Ivy repositories
	> It supports Grovy based Domain Specific Languages (DSL)

	> Install gradle from here
		https://gradle.org/gradle-download/
	> unzip --> set GRADLE_HOME to unzip fdir
	> in bashrc set path to gradle-3.1/bin
	

	> Build maven project with gradle
		1. in rooot dir -> gradle init
		2. 		-> gradle build

	> It generates some files
		1. build.gradle => Declare dependencies and plugins etc.
		2. gradlew
		3. gradlew.bat
		4. settings.gradle

	> gradle tasks
		=> Shows tasks that can be executed

	> 
